description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you passionate about patient safety, risk management, clinical governance and improving the quality of patient care? Are you an experienced manager with a strong knowledge of patient safety standards, principles and methodologies?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then Leeds and York NHS Partnership Foundation Trust would love to hear from you. Our vision is to provide outstanding specialist mental health and learning disability services as an employer of choice; we offer services across Leeds and York as well Regional and National specialist services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Clinical Governance Team provides services that fall within the profile of responsibility of the Executive Director of Nursing, Professions and Quality. The team is responsible for the central management of:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Patient Safety - Incident and Serious Incident Management, CAS alerts, Risk Register, patient safety meetings, Inquests; and the mortality process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PALS, Concerns, Complaints, Compliments and Litigation Claims&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Datix administration, quality assurance checks and support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Associated training and support for the above&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;External visits and inspections&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CQC liaison, administration and CQC Project Group&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting service lines in all fields&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Production of the Quality Account and monitoring of the associated quality improvement priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Policies and procedures relating to the above&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reporting to associated groups and committees; and Board business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a talented individual to join our leadership team. You will support the Directorate to enhance and develop high standards of safe care and quality through patient safety incident response management, risk management and continuous quality improvement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role involves undertaking Patient Safety incident investigations and reviews, mortality and other reviews; working as either lead or expert advisor. You will provide leadership, support and education to multidisciplinary staff involved to ensure the continued development of associated skills within the wider workforce.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also be working closely with multidisciplinary staff to ensure mandatory Clinical Risk training is developed and delivered in accordance with the Trust’s Clinical Risk Assessment and Management Procedure; and quality-assure and monitor training to ensure best practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Line-management of Clinical Governance team members is also included within the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note: applicants will be required to evidence that they meet the essential requirements of the role, as detailed in the person specification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous applicants need not apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rebecca Le-Hair on 07970 905054.&lt;/p&gt;
